## Workflow

```bash
[INSTALL_COMMAND]
bun harness:orchestrator
bun harness:orchestrate
bun harness:orchestrate --json
bun harness:advance
bun harness:stage --status
bun harness:sync-backlog
bun harness:scope-change --preview
bun .harness/state.ts --show
bun harness:env
bun harness:validate --phase EXECUTING
```

Use `bun .harness/orchestrator.ts` when you want a read-only preview of the next agent or task packet. Use `bun harness:orchestrate` when the parent runtime should consume a real launch cycle from `.harness/launches/latest.json`.

Harness Engineering and Orchestrator organizes requirements, architecture, progress, and validation into modular documents:

- `apps/` and `packages/`: default monorepo workspace foundation
- `docs/prd/`: requirements modules
- `docs/architecture/`: architecture modules
- `docs/progress/`: progress modules
- `docs/ai/`: AI execution guidance

Runtime auto-dispatch currently covers `project-discovery`, `MARKET_RESEARCH`, `TECH_STACK`, `prd-architect`, `scaffold-generator`, the UI design loop, `EXECUTING`, `VALIDATING`, and `context-compactor`.
After an interactive phase is complete, advance the lifecycle with `bun harness:advance`.
`bun harness:autoflow` advances only after the current phase's required outputs exist; if scaffold artifacts are missing, it stops and surfaces the missing phase work instead of skipping ahead. During `EXECUTING`, it auto-compacts and merges `REVIEW` milestones. At `COMPLETE`, it writes a final compact snapshot before surfacing context health. When the current delivery version is fully merged, it stops at a deploy review gate instead of auto-starting the next version.
If product scope changes inside the current delivery version, update the PRD first and run `bun harness:sync-backlog`, or use `bun harness:scope-change --apply` to apply + sync in one step.
If the next delivery version is ready after deploy / real-world review, update PRD / Architecture and run `bun harness:stage --promote V[N]`.

